I think the landscaping analogy is stronger than it first appears, because both businesses share the same underlying economics:

* Recurring service
* Route density
* Low customer acquisition cost once a neighborhood is won
* Equipment-intensive but not labor-intensive
* Easy to inspect quality
* Difficult for homeowners to justify doing themselves

The trick is not to think of yourself as a trash can cleaner.

Think of yourself as a Neighborhood Sanitation Service.

