One strategic addition

If I were designing this from scratch today, I’d treat the trash can cleaning as the “anchor service.” Once you have a trusted monthly visit and a route through a neighborhood, you can layer on adjacent recurring services with similar economics—pressure washing common areas, dumpster enclosure cleaning, dog waste station maintenance, mailbox kiosk cleaning, and even holiday or bulk-trash cleanup. The long-term asset isn’t the pressure washer; it’s the recurring neighborhood relationship and the optimized route.

That shifts the business from “the company that cleans trash cans” to a recurring neighborhood exterior sanitation platform, which is a broader and more defensible position as you grow.